<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interviewed on `Itogi' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002185194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1833 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002185194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 20 Feb -- There will be no air strike by 
NATO air forces on Bosnian Serb positions tonight, as envisaged 
by the North Atlantic bloc's ultimatum. Russian Defense 
Minister Pavel Grachev said this in an interview today on NTV 
television's "Itogi" program. He noted that that "this had 
become quite clear" after his telephone conversation today with 
U.S. Defense Secretary William Perry. 

</TEXT>

