<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Perry Refuses Peacekeepers for Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102191094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1846 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2102191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 21 TASS -- Russian Defence Minister 
Pavel Grachev invited the United States to send its 
peace-keepers to Sarajevo to patrol Muslim positions, but U.S. 
Defence Secretary William Perry refused. 
  Grachev told his U.S. counterpart during a telephone 
conversation on Monday that "the position of the Muslim side 
regarding the NATO demands and the presence of the Russian force 
in Sarajevo is not clear for Russia" and warned that any 
provocations against the Russian peace-keepers would result in 
"a sharp aggravation of the situation and will disrupt mutual 
efforts." 
  The presence of U.S. peace-keepers in Muslim areas "would 
strengthen the situation in general and we could have ensured a 
close interaction between our servicemen," Grachev said. 
  However, Perry rejected the invitation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

