<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Holds News Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102212494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1851 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2102212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev agreed with 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin on the necessity for political 
settlement of the Bosnian conflict which might be worked out 
during a special summit between the leaders of Russia, the U.S., 
France, Great Britain and Germany. Pavel Grachev held a press 
conference after his telephone conversation with U.S. Secretary 
of Defense, William Perry, on Monday. 
  According to diplomatic sources, the heads of the diplomatic 
missions of the U.S., France, Great Britain, Germany and some 
other states were discussing the possible summit on settlement 
of the crisis in Bosnia. This summit might take place in a 
European capital in the nearest future, the same sources said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

