<H3> <TI>   `Blue Helmets' Contingent Arrives in Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002174294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1656 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Kondrashov] </F>
  [Excerpts] Belgrade, 20 Feb -- The Russian contingent of 
"Blue Helmets" arrived in Sarajevo today. A convoy of several 
dozen APCs [armored personnel carriers] and trucks has completed 
a 250-km march from near Vucovar along Bosnia's snow-bound roads 
and across several difficult spots in the mountains. [passage 
omitted] 
  The 400 Russian" Blue Helmets" sent to Sarajevo will be 
stationed in Lukavica, a district in Sarajevo. As of Monday [21 
February] they will conduct military patrols along the 
disengagement lines and in the areas where their heavy guns, 
which are being brought under UN control, are concentrated. 

</TEXT>

