<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Arrives in Hungary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002230694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2214 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002230694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Zhirnikhin] </F>
  [Text] Budapest, 21 Feb -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev is to begin a working visit to Hungary today [21 
February]. He will visit Budapest during his tour of the 
countries of the Visegrad group which include Hungary, Poland, 
and the Czech and Slovak Republics. 
  The head of the Russian foreign policy department will hold 
talks with his Hungarian counterpart, Geza Jeszenszky, and will 
meet Hungarian President Arpad Goencz and Prime Minister Peter 
Boross. 
  In the opinion of the Hungarian side, apart from the 
development of bilateral ties, the talks will discuss, above 
all, relations between Hungary and NATO, the participation of 
the countries of Eastern Europe in the Partnership for Peace 
program, and ways of resolving the Bosnian crisis. 

</TEXT>

