<H3> <TI>   Concludes Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1802133894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1213 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1802133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yelena Yugina] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg February 18 TASS -- Bundeswehr 
General Klaus Naumann wound up his visit to Russia by meeting 
this country's military leaders and seeing sights in St. 
Petersburg, Russia's second city. 
  During his talks with the Leningrad Military District 
commander, Colonel-General Sergey Seleznev, the two generals 
agreed that considerable progress has been made in military 
political relations between Germany and Russia, including new, 
mutual beneficial forms of partnership. Germany is, for 
example, assisting the North- Western Military District in 
building housing for Russian troops withdrawn from Germany. 
  The Russian general spoke about his country's participation 
in the Partnership for Peace program, and stressed that 
cooperation between the two countries was of vital importance 
for stabilisation in Europe as a whole. 
  Both generals agreed that it was necessary to look for a 
peaceful settlement of the conflict in Bosnia. 
  The Bundeswehr general visited the city's historical and 
cultural landmarks, including museums and theatres, and the 
Piskarevskoye memorial cemetery where he put wreaths and flowers 
at the tombs of the victims of the Nazi blockade of Leningrad. 
  Klaus Naumann will be leaving for Bonn later today. 

</TEXT>

