<H3> <TI>   Georgian Premier Holds Economic Talks in Yerevan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2102200394 Yerevan Radio Yerevan International Service in 
Armenian 1630 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2102200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Radio Yerevan International Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Georgian Prime Minister Otar Patsatsia arrived in 
Yerevan today. During a meeting at the Armenian Government 
offices, the Armenian Prime Minister Grant Bagratyan and Otar 
Patsatsia discussed economic cooperation between the two 
countries, including the gas supply, protection of the gas 
pipeline, train transportation, and other matters of mutual 
interest. 
  The Armenian Deputy Prime Minister Vigen Chitechyan, and 
State Minister Gagik Shahbazyan also took part in the meeting. 
  The Georgian prime minister left Yerevan today. 

</TEXT>

