<H3> <TI>   `Dozens' Killed in `Heavy' Karabakh Fighting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1802175194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1616 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1802175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ARMENPRESS correspondent -- TASS] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan, 18 Feb -- Heavy fighting is continuing in 
the north of Karabakh. An ARMENPRESS correspondent was told in 
the defense headquarters of the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic that 
today Karabakh units succeeded in repulsing the enemy and drove 
them back beyond the Omar pass. The Azerbaijanis left dozens of 
dead on the field of battle. 
  Azerbaijani forces today again attacked in the Mardakert 
Rayon sector. Karabakh units are containing the attacks. Other 
sections of the front are relatively quiet. 

</TEXT>

