<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Starts Duties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102102894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0935 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 21 Feb -- Four hundred Russian airborne 
assault troops from the peacemaking battalion deployed in the 
Serbian Krajina (Croatia) have today started to carry out their 
duties in the buffer zone between the confronting sides near 
Sarajevo. The settlements where the Russian "Blue Helmets" are 
to be accommodated will also be named today. An ITAR-TASS 
correspondent was told this by the press service of the airborne 
assault troops. 
  According to the same source the Russian subunits, which 
arrived on Sunday evening in the area set by the United Nations 
for separating the sides, were met by Vitaliy Churkin, the 
Russian president's special envoy, by Russian Airborne Forces 
commander Colonel General Yevgeniy Podkolzin, and by his 
peacekeeping force deputy, Major General Nikolay Staskov. 
  In conjunction with the UN forces command they are to 
resolve 
the issue of the need to strengthen Russian peacekeeping forces 
in this region. 

</TEXT>

