<H3> <TI>   Baltic Military Exercises Completed; Commander Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2302113194 Tallinn ETA in English 0827 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2302113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From 23 February HOMMIKULEHT, PAEVALEHT, pp 1,3; "News </F>
Bulletin" No. 37/94] 
  [Text] Wednesday, February 23 -- Colonel Arvo Sirel, 
commander of the Estonian-Latvian-Lithuanian joint manoeuvre 
completed near Vdru yesterday, stressed that the exercise served 
its purpose. He admitted that the exercise was largely 
conditional and that the terrain was chosen in the interest of 
visibility. 
  The exercise proved the capability of the Baltic soldiers to 
operate jointly. Further development of cooperation should 
concern the unification of communication, tactical control, 
coast guard and air defence, head of the Lithuanian GHQ training 
section Colonel Romas ibas said. 
  Finnish, Swedish, Norwegian and British military attaches 
observed the exercise. 

</TEXT>

