<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former KGB Staffer Fails To Incriminate Baburin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2202133594 Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN in Russian 19 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2202133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [ROS-INFORMBYURO report: "Stop Press..."] </F>
  [Text] Former general of Soviet political intelligence 
Oleg Kalugin, who is on trial for spreading false reports about 
the alleged existence of "collusion" between the KGB and the 
well-known public and state figure Sergey Baburin, has been 
unable to present any documentary evidence of his public 
"exposures." 
  For six months he failed to appear at Kuntsevskiy Rayon 
Court 
in the city of Moscow, where legal action to defend the honor 
and dignity of the State Duma deputy and leader of the Russian 
All-National Union is in progress against O. Kalugin and the 
newspaper IZVESTIYA. On Tuesday 15 February the defendant 
appeared before the court. During the hearing he basically 
confirmed that his action was prompted by political motives: He 
had to discredit Baburin. 
  Addressing the court, Sergey Baburin reminded those present 
that "Kalugin's slanderous statements were reproduced by dozens 
and dozens of mass media sources, to be relished and publicly 
commented on by his political opponents." But he has not yet 
received any apology for the offending article. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

