<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Convinced of Army Loyalty to Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202200494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1915 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow February 23 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin said on Wednesday he is convinced that the national 
armed forces will remain loyal to the constitution and pledged 
to ensure social benefits for the military. 
  "I am convinced that the personnel of the Russian Armed 
Forces will remain loyal to the constitution, the military oath 
and duty, cherish the military rank and army comradeship", 
Yeltsin said in a message of greetings to the armed forces and 
war veterans on the occasion of the day of motherland defenders 
marked on February 23. 
  "The armed forces are a core of the Russian statehood, 
guarantor of peace, stability and democratic gains. They should 
be powerful, mobile and equipped with the most efficient 
armaments. The state will do everything to increase the 
prestige of military profession and make servicemen and members 
of their families feel better protected in the social sphere," 
the president added. 
  "The day of motherland defenders is a special holiday. It is 
marked by the entire people, who pay tribute and show respect 
and gratitude to Russian servicemen. 
  "Russian servicemen were the first to counteract forces, 
which tried to destroy our state with fire and sword and enslave 
our people. They saved Russia in the most difficult, mortally 
dangerous moments of war. 
  "You, the servicemen of the armed forces, are worthy heirs 
and successors of military traditions. At a time of trial you 
show restraint and firmness and honestly fulfill the 
professional and civic duty. 
  "I wish you, dear servicemen, your dear and near, veterans 
and civilian personnel of the armed forces, health, happiness 
and prosperity. Glory, honor and gratitude to you for your hard 
work and success to you in life and military service!" says the 
message. 

</TEXT>

