<H3> <TI>   Turkmenistan To Restore Gas Supply </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202221294 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2100 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202221294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- Ukrainian Deputy Prime Minister Valentyn 
Landyk, has informed a UNIAN correspondent that a telephone 
conversation took place on 22 February between Acting Prime 
Minister Yuhym Zvyahilskyy and representatives of the Turkmen 
Government on the matter of the suspension of the gas supply 
from Turkmenistan to Ukraine. 
  Following the Ukrainian side's reasoning that: "No one has 
done this before. If God has given you gas, it is not worth 
abusing this," a preliminary accord was reached on selling 
60,000 tonnes of wheat to Turkmenistan to credit the debt and 
payment by Ukraine of $50 million of the 150 million debt. 
After this, it is likely that the supply of gas to Ukraine will 
be resumed. 

</TEXT>

