<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Georgian Premier Discusses Gas Supplies With Armenia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2202190594 Yerevan SNARK in English 1454 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2202190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, February 22 (SNARK) -- Today the details of 
the yesterday's visit of Otar Patsatsia, the Georgian 
prime-minister, to Armenia became known. He has met with Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan, the Armenian president, and Grant Bagratyan, the 
prime-minister of Armenia. Today Vahan Papazyan, the foreign 
minister, told reporters about the negotiation. According to 
him Armenia in contrast to Georgia and other CIS's countries 
hasn't got debts for gas supplied by Turkmenistan. 
  The minister said that Armenia is ready to give half of the 
gas purchasing in Turkmenistan to Georgia, however, in return 
for it, Georgia must provide unimpeded passing of loads for 
Armenia through its territory, including the loads from the 
ports of Poti and Batumi. According to Vahan Papazyan, Otar 
Patsatsia wasn't ready to accept the proposals of Armenian 
party. But Vahan Papazyan expressed the hope that after 
appropriate consultations the political authorities of Georgia 
will accept the proposal suggested by Armenia. 

</TEXT>

