<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Combat Activity in Nagorno-Karabakh Resumes After Lull </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2202221194 Yerevan SNARK in English 1530 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2202221194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, February 22 (SNARK) -- Active combats 
have resumed today in a number of places on the 
Karabakh-Azerbaijan confrontation line. As told to SNARK by the 
Karabakh Defence Army press-service, Azerbaijani troops 
undertook since morning Feb. 22 an offensive in Martuniskiy and 
Fizoulinskiy directions, at the Eastern and South-Eastern battle 
areas. By the noon data, here combats were started in process 
of which the Karabakh forces were able to neutralize the enemy's 
efforts. As yet there is no information of losses. At the same 
time, artillery shelling of Karabakh Army positions is made in 
suburbs of regional center Mardakert. Karabakh side undertook 
counter actions. 

</TEXT>

