this matter from inside Georgia was accepted. 
  In briefing the guests about the grave situation existing in 
the republic as a result of the six-year-old aggression by 
Armenia, Azerbaijani Prime Minister Suret Guseynov said that 
despite all the difficulties Azerbaijan will not withhold its 
assistance to Georgia, with whom it has lived in friendship for 
centuries. 
  Suret Guseynov also touched upon the problems of our more 
than half a million compatriots living in Georgia, and hoped 
that the Georgian Government will do everything to solve their 
problems. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Abbas Abbasov and Economy Minister 
Samed Sadykhov also took part in the meeting. 

