<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attacks Across Border Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302110994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1026 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2302110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe February 23 TASS -- Despite Dushanbe's call 
on the Afghan leadership to take steps to avert acts of armed 
provocation against sovereign Tajikistan and Russian border 
troops from Afghan territory, the village of Sarigor in 
Tajikistan's south was again shelled on Tuesday night, according 
to sources in the information department of Tajikistan's 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs. 
  According to the same source, the Russian border troops 
responded by devastating fire which destroyed a mixed group of 
Tajik opposition militants and Afghan mojahedin near the 12 
border post of the Moscow border unit. The Russian border 
troops are fully in control of the area now. 
  Along with this the source in Tajikistan's Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs cited the command of the Russian border troops 
in Tajikistan as saying that more Tajik opposition militants 
have been observed concentrating near the Afghan city of 
Talukan, province of Tahor, and moving towards the border. The 
source did not rule out the possibility of a new act of armed 
provocation against the Russian border troops in the region. 

</TEXT>

