<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rakhmanov Makes Armed Forces Day Address </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202120494 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Russian 
1000 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Address by Supreme Council Chairman Imamali Rakhmanov to </F>
Armed Forces staff on the occasion of Armed Forces Day; date not 
given -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] Dear comrades, the people of the Republic of 
Tajikistan will ceremonially mark the anniversary of the 
creation of the Armed Forces of the Republic of Tajikistan on 23 
February [1994]. 
  The Armed Forces of the republic were formed in the 
extremely 
difficult conditions of the social and political situation, and 
the civil war. The first units of the Armed Forces that were 
formed during a short period of time, together with the military 
units of the Internal Affairs and Security Ministries of the 
Republic of Tajikistan, made a huge contribution to the 
stabilization of the social and political situation and 
strengthening the defense capability of the republic. 
  The people of the Republic of Tajikistan will remember 
forever the names of those soldiers and commanders of the Armed 
Forces who were killed in actions for the noble cause, the 
freedom and independence of their motherland. 
  I congratulate you, dear comrades on the occasion of the 
anniversary of creation of the Armed Forces of the Republic of 
Tajikistan. I wish you sound health, happiness, and success. I 
am confident that the Command and the Staff of the Armed Forces 
of the Republic of Tajikistan will do their best to protect and 
to promote the independence, sovereignty, and territorial 
integrity of the Republic of Tajikistan. 
  [Signed] Imamali Rakhmanov, the head of state and Supreme 
Council chairman of the Republic of Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

