<H3> <TI>   Parliament Postpones Government Confirmation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202171894 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1530 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, 22 Feb -- IBERIA reports that at a meeting 
of the Georgian parliament today, Head of State Eduard 
Shevardnadze said that, owing to a grave energy crisis, the 
confirmation of the composition of the acting government should 
be postponed until 15 March. The majority of parliamentarians, 
including those from opposition factions, supported this 
proposal. 

</TEXT>

