<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troops Repulse Attack From Abkhaz Separatists </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202234294 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 2050 
GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202234294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY reports that despite 
the talks under way in Geneva, the Abkhaz separatists and their 
North Caucasian mercenaries are launching attacks from the Lata 
tunnels [the tunnels linking the Abkhaz-held plain with the 
Georgian-held eastern Abkhazian mountains] against the Georgian 
home guard in Abkhazian Svaneti. 
  The latest attack began at (?1020) on 22 February. After 
fierce fighting, the home guard repulsed the attack. At 1130, 
(?a vehicle) appeared near positions of the Georgian home guard, 
which they destroyed. Cossacks were found inside it. None of 
the Georgian home guard were killed. 
  All attempts by the Abkhaz separatists [words indistinct] 
are 
met with stiff resistance [words indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

