<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gas Pipeline Security Linked to Russian Mediation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2202173794 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 22 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2202173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Vitaliy Denisov report under "In Brief" rubric: "Does Gas </F>
Supply to Armenia Depend on Russian Military Too?"] 
  [Text] Tbilisi -- Yet again the gas pipeline supplying gas 
to Armenia has been blown up on Georgian territory. The 
Armenian Government has delivered a statement to the Georgian 
Government protesting that, despite repeated assurances, the 
Georgian authorities are not taking resolute measures to prevent 
such incidents. Many people in Armenia are linking the future 
security of the only gas main via which fuel is delivered to 
this country with a mediator's role for Russian troops. 

</TEXT>

