<H3> <TI>   Makes Key Appointments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202184494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1432 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Belarusian Parliament today approved 43-year-old 
Ivan Bambiza as deputy parliament speaker. 
  Bambiza was born in the Gomel Region, graduated from the 
agricultural institute in 1975. He occupies the post of 
secretary of the planning and budget and financial commission of 
the republic's parliament. 
  The parliament has approved Gennadiy Levitskiy as chairman 
of 
the KGB committee. Earlier General Levitskiy was deputy 
chairman of the KGB, then chief of the counterintelligence 
service. 
  First Vice-Premier Mikhail Myasnikovich proposed to appoint 
Vladimir Danko as Belarusian Interior Minister, who earlier 
worked as First Deputy Interior Minister. Danko was approved as 
Interior Minister by a majority vote. 

</TEXT>

