<H3> <TI>   NATO Military Inspection Team Arrives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102154594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1335 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2102154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By BELINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk February 21 TASS -- In accordance with the 
treaty on conventional armed forces in Europe, the NATO military 
inspection under the flag of West [as received] Germany has 
begun working on the base for storage of military equipment 
located near the city of Borisov in Belarus. 
  The place of inspection was chosen by the NATO experts 
themselves an hour after their arrival to the Minsk-2 Airport as 
it is stipulated by the treaty. At the present time NATO 
inspectors examine and count units of materiel on the base. 
  Arriving together with a group of inspectors from West 
Germany, Belgium, Denmark and the Netherlands were also chief of 
the Bundeswehr center for problems of control, Brigadier General 
Heinz Lokwai, and deputy of the Bundestag, Dr. Gunther Mueller. 
They will familiarize themselves with the process of destroying 
tanks and infantry combat vehicles at the Borisov tank repairs 
plant which is being carried out also in accordance with the 
treaty. 
  The inspection is due to complete its work on February 22. 

</TEXT>

