<H3> <TI>   Government's Additional Powers Confirmed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202232894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1950 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202232894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Belarusian parliament constitutionally confirmed 
the additional powers granted to the government. The 
parliament's session on Tuesday adopted a decision under which 
the prime minister was granted the authority to alter the 
composition of the government, to appoint and discharge the 
government's members coordinating the decisions with the Supreme 
Soviet's presidium and the appropriate parliamentary commissions. 
  However, the Supreme Council preserved the powers to appoint 
and to discharge the leaders of the power structures and the 
foreign minister, an Interfax correspondent in Minsk reported. 

</TEXT>

