<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Khasbulatov Guard Arrested, Said Preparing `Base' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2202131394 Moscow TRUD in Russian 18 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2202131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow TRUD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Khasbulatov's Guard Arrested"] </F>
  [Text] Estonian security police and an MVD special subunit 
have arrested Aleksandr Denisov, who was on the wanted list for 
organizing mass disturbances in Moscow last October, in the 
Estonian city of Johvi. 
  When he was arrested Denisov, who guarded Khasbulatov and 
Rutskoy, was found to be carrying a Tokarev pistol. The 
detainee testified that he was preparing "a base for around 20 
people connected with the October events in Russia" in northeast 
Estonia. 
  Before moving to Russia Denisov worked in the Estonian city 
of Kohtla-Jarve in the Criminal Investigations Department and 
later in Tallinn in the Organized Crime Department. 

</TEXT>

