<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brazauskas Urges Peaceful Resolution in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2302110694 Vilnius ELTA in English 2243 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2302110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Statement by President Brazauskas About Conflict in </F>
Bosnia;" From "News Bulletin" No. 442] 
  [Text] Vilnius, Feb 22, ELTA -- After NATO had threatened 
Bosnia with air strikes, heavy weapons were withdrawn from 
Sarajevo. The efforts of United Nations, NATO, international 
organizations and the biggest countries to eliminate the Bosnian 
conflict produced the results. We support the idea of passing 
Sarajevo's administration to United Nations and expansion of the 
peace zones in other parts of Bosnia. 
  Although Lithuania is separated from Bosnia by more than a 
thousand kilometres, we are not indifferent to the senseless 
massacre in Europe. Unfortunately, in some other European 
countries the situation is not stable as well, so similar 
conflicts should be prevented beforehand. 
  Lithuania is interested in peaceful, but determined and more 
coordinated actions of the international community in regulating 
the conflict in Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

