<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fifth Round of Talks Held on Agreement With Poland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2302111994 Vilnius ELTA in English 2243 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2302111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 442] </F>
  [Text] Warsaw, Feb 22, ELTA -- On Tuesday the fifth and, 
hopefully, the last Lithuanian-Polish negotiation round for the 
bilateral agreement was held at the Polish Foreign Ministry. 
The negotiations were headed by the Foreign Vice-Ministers 
Vladislavas Domarkas and Iwo Byczevski. 
  On the eve of the negotiations Byczevski said that he hoped 
to reach the final solution of all disputable questions. He 
added that there would not be a separate declaration on the 
Vilnius region annexation in 1920. Byczevski also noted that 
Poland would point out requirements of the Polish minority in 
Lithuania in the agreement. 
  Members of Lithuanian state delegation also told ELTA that 
there would not be a separate declaration, but historical 
aspects important for the both countries would be mentioned in 
the preamble of the agreement. 
  On Tuesday [22 February] Polish Catholic daily THE SLOWO 
published an open letter from the federation of the Polish who 
live in the border territories in Poland (the Kreis 
organizations) to Polish prime minister. They required to 
consider the part of the agreement concerning the rights of the 
Polish minority in Lithuania in the Polish-Lithuanian 
negotiations. 

</TEXT>

