<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Agreements Signed With Kyrgyzstan, Kazakhstan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202151394 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1300 GMT 22 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A working group, including officials from the 
Economics Ministry, the Foreign Affairs Ministry, and the Bank 
of Latvia has returned from a visit to Kazakhstan and 
Kyrgyzstan. A Latvian-Kyrgyz Government agreement (for 
indefinite time) on the principles of trade and economic 
cooperation, which provides for a mutually favorable procedure, 
was initialled in Kyrgyzstan. In addition, a protocol and its 
supplements were signed on reciprocal supplies of goods for this 
year. 
  Kyrgyzstan wishes to receive from Latvia minibuses, spare 
parts for motorcars and tractors, shoes, synthetic threads, as 
well as consumer goods. For its part Kyrgyzstan will supply to 
Latvia washed wool, woolen yarn, fermented tobacco and other 
goods, and raw materials. 
  The text of an agreement on the principles of trade and 
economic cooperation, and a protocol of supplies were 
coordinated with Kazakhstan. Supplements to the protocol were 
signed. This agreement will be initialled in the very near 
future. 
  Latvia will receive from Kazakhstan coal from Karaganda, pig 
iron, tin plate, which is needed for producers of tinned fish 
and dairy products, and rolled nonferrous metals. After 
additional coordination by the governments of the two countries, 
the supply of wheat from Kazakhstan is also possible. 
  A visit of the working group to Uzbekistan, as well as to 
Tajikistan and Turkmenistan to coordinate and sign protocols of 
reciprocal supplies are scheduled for the beginning of March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

