<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Aide Comments on Serbs Diplomatic Efforts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1902140094 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1200 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1902140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Exclusive" interview with presidential aide Dmitriy </F>
Ryurikov by correspondent Sergey Mikhaliov; place and date not 
given; from the "Novosti" newscast -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Mikhailov] The Serbs have already shown their 
response to Russia's request--if I may call it so--and started 
to withdraw their weapons, but they were rather cautious of the 
similar demands issued by the UN. How would you explain this? 
  [Ryurikov] Well you know, I can only say it was simply a 
matter of knowing how to negotiate, of using convincing 
arguments, finding the right tone at the right moment, and 
generally being well-skilled in the art of diplomacy. I think 
that for all these reasons our arguments were accepted this time. 
  [Mikhailov] But there are still the Muslims and Croatians. 
What will they do now? 
  [Ryurikov] We hope that they respond with goodwill gestures 
to the goodwill gesture. We also hope that our partners 
involved in the settlement of this conflict who work in close 
contact with them will ensure this in the same way as we did our 
work. 

</TEXT>

