<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Holds Talks With Goncz, Boross </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202144494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1425 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Sergey Zhirnikhin, </F>
Georgiy Shmelyov] 
  [Text] Budapest February 22 TASS -- Hungarian President 
Arpad Goncz congratulated Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev, currently here on a working visit, on success of the 
Russian initiative for peaceful Bosnian settlement. 
  He said the initiative has saved the world from troubles, 
sufferings and escalation of combat operations in former 
Yugoslavia. In the words of Goncz, the major Russian political 
success consolidated its international authority and position on 
the world scene and enabled NATO to overcome the post-ultimatum 
situation with dignity. 
  Goncz reminded Kozyrev of his latest meeting with Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin when the Hungarian state head said 
Russia will continue to play a key role in solution of European 
problems. 
  On the same day, Kozyrev was received by Hungarian Prime 
Minister Peter Boross. The premier praised Russian diplomatic 
efforts to settle situation around Sarajevo and said decisive 
and constructive Russian efforts enabled Hungary to overcome a 
difficult situation, as it is geographically close to the 
Yugoslav conflict zone. 

</TEXT>

