<DOCNO> FBIS3-37802 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov036_a_94026" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-036 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Ready for Partnerhip Talks `At Any Time' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102171194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1606 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2102171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature] </F>
  [Text] Moscow is prepared to start talks on joining the 
"Partnership for Peace" program at any time, a senior member of 
Russia's Foreign Ministry told Interfax on Monday [21 February]. 
  According to him, the conference that was to be held between 
Russian and NATO experts on Monday has again been postponed 
because of developments in the Balkans. 
  Russia would like to clarify some issues before joining the 
NATO program, Interfax's interviewee said. "This is why the 
upcoming conference will have the nature of a briefing," he 
noted. NATO experts will have to elucidate their vision of 
Russia's participation in the partnership program," he said. 

</TEXT>

