<H3> <TI>   Further on Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2102101394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0400 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2102101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As reported in the Republic's media, a working 
meeting between Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich and 
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin was held on 18 
February in Moscow. Summarizing the results of the meeting, the 
two prime ministers emphasized that this was a final discussion 
on the mechanisms for both countries' functioning under a single 
monetary system. At the prime ministers' request, groups of 
experts will complete drafting documents in two or three days. 
On the Belarusian side, the government team is headed by CIS 
Executive Secretary Uladzimir Zalamay. The final signing of the 
documents is expected in the near future. 
  At the meeting, the main principles of unification of the 
monetary systems were outlined -- absolute unification of the 
price policy and mutually beneficial exchange rates of 
currencies of both states. 

</TEXT>

