<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Cordial' Talks Held </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2202103794 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0855 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2202103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 22 Feb (INA)--An Iraqi delegation led by 
Foreign Ministry Undersecretary Riyad al-Qaysi held two rounds 
of talks last night with Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Boris 
Kolokolov at the Russian Foreign Ministry. 
  Al-Qaysi told an INA correspondent in Moscow that he briefed 
the Russian side on Iraq's talks with the Special Commission, 
the UN Security Council members, and the International Atomic 
Energy Agency, and on Iraq's implementation of its commitments 
as stipulated by the UN Security Council resolutions, 
particularly Resolution 715 on future monitoring. 
  He indicated that the two sides also discussed the subject 
of 
developing bilateral relations, particularly in the political 
and economic fields. They agreed to continue dialogue and 
consultation, in addition to discussing methods of bilateral 
cooperation within the framework of the Russian movement in the 
UN Security Council. 
  Al-Qaysi stressed that the atmosphere of the talks was 
extremely cordial. 

</TEXT>

