<H3> <TI>   Duma Votes For Amnesty for Coup Participants </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302115094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aleksandr Ruvinskiy] </F>
  [Text] I have just come into the studio to report important 
news to our listeners: The session of the State Duma has just 
passed a resolution. According to this, four documents are 
endorsed as a single package, including a resolution on an 
amnesty for those who took part in the events of August 1991, 1 
May 1993, and September-October 1994. 
  Some deputies, in particular from the Agrarian faction, the 
Communist Party faction and the Liberal Democratic Party faction 
have described this as the biggest occasion for celebration in 
the history of the Russian state. 
  Other deputies, in particular those from the Russia's Choice 
faction, said that this was the start of civil war in Russia. 

</TEXT>

