<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Groups Protest Continued Russian Tenure of Skrunda </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202172794 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1400 GMT 22 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202172794 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Latvian National Independence Movement [LNNK], 
the alliance For the Fatherland and Freedom, the People's Front 
of Latvia, the Latvian Green Party, the Latvian Christian 
Democratic Union, the Environment Protection Club, the Latvian 
National Soldiers' Society, the Latvian National Union of 
Falcons of the Daugava, the Latvian Association of the 
Politically Repressed, the Livonian Association and the Latvian 
National Partisans' Union, all of which are participant groups 
in the union of Latvian National Forces, have signed a protest 
statement against the maintenance of the Skrunda radar station 
in Latvia for another five and a half years. This was announced 
today at a news conference by Baiba Petersone, deputy chairman 
of the LNNK board. 
  The Union of National Forces calls on the Latvian government 
delegation, the Saeima, and the state president not to accept a 
treaty with Russia if it even partly legitimizes Russia's 
military presence in Latvia. Otherwise, the statement says, the 
Union of National Forces envisages using the forms of direct 
democracy and the experience of non-violent resistance until the 
full withdrawal of a foreign country's troops. 

</TEXT>

