<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Negotiators Issue 
Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302231694 Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY in Russian 
1457 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302231694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It has emerged that yesterday, the Geneva talks on 
the peaceful settlement of the conflict in Abkhazia examined the 
problem of the return of the refugees to their original places 
of residence and Abkhazia's political status. 
  Representatives of leading Western powers present at the 
talks reaffirmed their position as regards Georgia's territorial 
integrity, telling [Abkhaz Supreme Soviet Chairman Vladislav] 
Ardzinba, who had been specially summoned to Geneva, that there 
could be no talk of Abkhazia's secession. 
  The Georgian delegation made a statement strongly condemning 
the Abkhaz separatists' actions against civilians in Gali Rayon. 
The text of the statement was distributed among representatives 
of the mass media. 
  Georgian representatives made special emphasis on the fact 
that the Abkhaz side had blocked a visit to Gali Rayon by the UN 
mission, which was confirmed by its leader, General Hvidegaard. 
  The talks continued today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

