<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Washington Demands Operatives Leave U.S. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MK2402082094 Moscow KURANTY in Russian 24 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2402082094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed INFORM-KURANTY comment: "They Sold America </F>
for 1.5 Million"] 
  [Text] Russia has been "driven into" a fresh scandal. Yet 
another "sweet couple" has been uncovered way across the 
Atlantic -- a high-ranking CIA man and his Colombian wife who 
provided the USSR and later Russia with information of interest 
to the KGB-Foreign Intelligence Service for regular remuneration. 
  The Clinton administration has naturally become very upset 
at 
Russia which, poor as it is, so unproductively spent $1.5 
million to buy the informers. Therefore, they in Washington are 
demanding that all persons having a hand in such an operation 
--that is, intelligence operatives -- should of their own 
accord, with no additional prompting, leave the United States. 
Otherwise, they say, we will take some measures. It is not 
ruled out that after such an affront, the Russian special 
services will announce the detention of an American informer. 
Traditions should be kept up. 

</TEXT>

