<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Churkin on `Political Coalition' To Solve Bosnia Crisis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302153294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1511 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2302153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Krylovich] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 23 TASS -- The creation of a 
"political coalition" to solve the crisis in Bosnia is the major 
result of the Bonn meeting of representatives of Foreign 
Ministries of Russia and the West, according to Russian envoy to 
former Yugoslavia Vitaliy Churkin who arrived from Bonn on 
Wednesday [23 February]. 
  "The meeting demonstrated a high level of coincidence in 
approaches and assessments regarding what is to be done in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina", he told reporters. 
  The political essence of the Bonn meeting will determine 
practical steps in the near future, according to Churkin who 
said that "now we have passed the crisis situation and are 
moving to intensive political contacts". 
  He stressed that it is important to avoid new crises in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

