<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shaposhnikov Praises Efforts To Avert NATO Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302152994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1512 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2302152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 23 TASS -- Participating in the 
Sarajevo settlement, Russia as a member of the world community 
has upgraded its own status, Marshal of the Russian Air Force 
Yevgeniy Shaposhnikov said in an interview with TASS on 
Wednesday [23 February]. He highly praised the efforts taken by 
the Russian president and diplomats for averting NATO threatened 
air strikes in Bosnia, noting that Russia "demonstrated its 
capability of moderating by peaceful means armed conflicts 
exhausting both big and small nations". 
  Shaposhnikov expressed sincere support of Russian soldiers 
serving now in the U.N. peacekeeping forces in former 
Yugoslavia, assessing their mission as a historic one. On day 
of Fatherland's defenders, the Marshal wished Russian 
servicemen, wherever they are staying at the moment -- in 
Serbia, Bosnia-Herzegovina or on Afghan border -- to be 
steadfast, self-controlled and to fulfil their military duty in 
the way Russians have always done, from the time of the battle 
of Kulikovo to the Great Patriotic War. 

</TEXT>

