<H3> <TI>   Concludes Visit to Poland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302170194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1514 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS special correspondents Aleksandr Potemkin and </F>
Georgiy Shmelev] 
  [Text] Krakow, 23 Feb -- The working visit to Poland by 
Andrey Kozyrev, foreign minister of the Russian Federation, 
ended with the laying of flowers on the grave of Soviet soldiers 
beside the walls of the old tower in the center of Krakow. The 
ceremony was also attended by representatives of the city 
authorities and by the inhabitants of the ancient capital of the 
Polish kings. 
  A. Kozyrev then headed for Balice airport, from where he 
left 
for home. The Russian minister was seen off by Polish 
officials, the president and governor of Krakow, and also by the 
Russian ambassador to Poland. 

</TEXT>

