<H3> <TI>   Georgian Premier Asks for Help To Ease Energy Crisis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2302205794 Baku TURAN in English 1909 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2302205794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Baku (February 23) TURAN--Yesterday Georgian 
Premier, Otar Patsatsia met with Azeri Premier, Suret Guseynov 
in Baku. During their meeting Georgian Premier made a request to 
Azerbaijan to assist to remove energy crisis in Georgia, reports 
press-service of Azerbaijani Cabinet. 
  Otar Patsatsia mentioned that last week Georgian Foreign 
Minister, Alexander Chikvaidze and Iranian leadership concluded 
the agreement concerning delivery of Iranian gas to Georgia. 
Georgian Premier wanted Azerbaijan to give a consent to 
transport gas through its territory. 
  Azeri Prime Minister Guseynov said that the meeting between 
President Aliyev and President Shevardnadze is due to take place 
in the nearest future. And presently Azerbaijan works out the 
package of documents stipulating establishment of 
Azerbaijani-Georgian cooperation, including providing energy 
assistance to Georgia. 
  Azeri Premier mentioned that Azerbaijan will deliver energy 
carriers to Georgia if it guarantees that they not be further 
sent to Armenia. Georgian Premier Patsatsia agreed to 
Azerbaijan's control over energy carriers transportation. 
  Suret Guseynov drew attention of Georgian Premier at the 
situation of Azeri minority in Georgia and asked the Georgian 
leadership to take measures to secure their civil rights. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

