<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Free Trade Agreement Talks Open in Brussels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302115594 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 0700 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Talks about a free trade agreement will begin today 
in Brussels between the European Union and Estonia. The 
Estonian delegation is led by Priit Kolbre, head of the Foreign 
Ministry's foreign trade policy department. The first round of 
talks will last one day, during which the delegations will 
clarify their opinions about the contents of the agreement. It 
is known already that the European Union will provide Estonia 
completely free trade in respect of industrial goods, textile 
products, and agricultural produce. 

</TEXT>

