<H3> <TI>   Arms Consignment Discovered Near Southeastern Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS2402111694 Tallinn BNS in English 2132 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2402111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Feb 23, BNS -- Estonian security police 
and armed forces in a joint operation on Feb. 21 discovered more 
than 500 TT pistols near Luhamaa at the country's southeastern 
border with Russia. 
  The guns were seized and handed over to the defense forces, 
said Juri Pihl, director general of the Defense Police. Pihl 
said nobody was arrested so far, but his department has 
initiated a criminal case on arms smuggling and misprision 
charges. 
  The criminal code foresees a jail sentence of 3 to 8 years 
for such crimes. 
  Russian customs in their checkpoint of Petseri, opposite 
Luhamaa, on Feb. 21 uncovered five guns and lots of cartridges 
in a car headed from Estonia to Russia. Those who were in the 
car have been arrested. 

</TEXT>

