<H3> <TI>   Poland's Walesa Arrives on `State Visit' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302114394 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1100 GMT 23 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Polish President Lech Walesa arrived in Latvia today 
for a state visit. The Polish president is accompanied by an 
official state delegation of advisers and experts. Walesa was 
met at the airport by Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis, Prime 
Minister Valdis Birkavs, Foreign Minister Georgs Andrejevs, 
Dainis Turlais, the commander of the Defense Forces, and foreign 
ambassadors accredited in Latvia. The presidents of the two 
countries attended a parade by the Latvian defense forces. 
  An hour ago at Riga Castle, Walesa and Ulmanis signed a 
joint 
political declaration on strengthening friendship and 
cooperation between Latvia and Poland, a declaration on the 
resumption of work of the agreements concluded between Latvia 
and Poland between 1922 and 1938--which provides for 
reconsideration and assessment of those documents--as well as an 
agreement on legal assistance between Latvia and Poland in 
civil, family, labor, and criminal cases. These documents were 
signed by Latvia's Foreign Minister Andrejevs and Iwo Byczewski, 
Polish deputy minister of foreign affairs. 

</TEXT>

