<H3> <TI>   Yakovlev Views Guidelines </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402121194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1149 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 24 TASS--President Yeltsin's address 
to the Federal Assembly "contains a rather powerful potential 
for putting into effect now the main guidelines of the domestic 
and foreign policy, which is the constitutional duty of the 
president," Aleksandr Yakovlev, official representative of 
President Yeltsin in parliament, told ITAR-TASS. 
  In his opinion, those guidelines should now be translated 
into legislative acts and in the steps to be taken by executive 
authorities. Then they will really become "actions with 
tangible results." 
  Yakovlev stressed that the putting into effect of the main 
guidelines is the task for all branches of authority. 
Legislation and its subsequent implementation should be the 
next stage. 
  The presidential address pointed to the absence of 
uniformity 
in the economic legislation and stressed that "a breakthrough in 
providing legal support for the market-oriented reform is 
urgently needed." 

</TEXT>

