<H3> <TI>   Kazannik To Free Coup Organizers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402091494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0910 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2402091494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 24 TASS--Russian Prosecutor General 
Alexey Kazannik is ready to free anti-Yeltsin rebels pardoned by 
the State Duma on Wednesday as soon as he receives the necessary 
documents from the legislature and talks to each of the 
organisers of the October armed opposition revolt and hard-line 
May Day demonstration last year. 
  "In case the accused agree with the (Duma) resolution I 
shall 
rule to drop criminal proceedings against each of the accused", 
Kazannik told TASS on Thursday. 
  If the accused refuse to be pardoned the criminal cases 
against them will proceed in a usual way, he added. 
  Kazannik said he had not yet received the Duma decision, but 
stressed that his office does not give political assessments to 
various laws. "It ensures lawfulness and a strict fulfillment of 
all instructions of competent state bodies", he said. 

</TEXT>

