<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko on Court's Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302153894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1451 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2302153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow February 23 TASS -- "It is only the court 
which can find the Lefortovo prisoners guilty or non-guilty", 
Federation Council Speaker Vladimir Shumeyko told reporters on 
Wednesday referring to October revolt organisers who were 
pardoned by the lower chamber of the parliament on Wednesday. 
  He stressed that the organisers are not political, but 
common 
criminals. "There are no political crimes or political prisoners 
in Russia", Shumeyko said. 
  The revolt organisers face criminal charges and it is only 
the court which can make the final verdict, according to 
Shumeyko who said that his upper chamber does not plan to 
discuss the amnesty. 

</TEXT>

