<H3> <TI>   Yakovlev: Amnesty Judicially Correct </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402115594 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The decision on the political amnesty of the SCSE 
[State Committee for the State of Emergency] members and the 
participants in the October events is completely in keeping with 
the Constitution from a judicial point of view. This was stated 
by Aleksandr Yakovlev, the official representative of the 
Russian president at the Federal Assembly today. However, he 
noted, the political and social aspects in this case are more 
important than the judicial one. He thinks that an act on 
amnesty may create a false illusion of hopes for civic peace. 

</TEXT>

