<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Su-34 Bomber Described in Weapons Feature </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302230994 Moscow Radio Moscow in Russian to Tajikistan 
1700 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302230994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Radio Slavyanka" program of the Russian Defense </F>
Ministry] 
  [Summary] Slavyanka is to run a regular feature on the 
fourth Wednesday of each month entitled "The Russian Arsenal" 
devoted to Russian advanced weaponry. 
  The Su-34 front-line bomber is to replace the Su-24 and 
Su-24M. It has a range of 4,000 km. Its on-board computer and 
other radio-electronic equipment with multiple back-ups can 
bring the aircraft to its destination in any weather conditions 
with a precision of one meter. Its homing missiles and bombs 
can be launched from a range of up to 250 km. The two-man crew 
sit alongside each other in a comfortable air-conditioned 
cockpit. It has an artificial intelligence, an active safety 
system which allows acrobatic maneuvers at a speed of 1,400 
km/hr and at very low altitudes. It can overcome air defense 
systems. The cockpit has 17-mm armor to defend the airmen from 
stray bullets. 
  Many of the aircraft's other features are still classified. 

</TEXT>

