<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Snegur Views Ties With Romania, Ilascu Case </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202171294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1400 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2202171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moldovan President Mircea Snegur received Eugen 
Preda, general director of the Romanian radio station, at his 
Chisinau residence today and gave an exclusive interview. 
  President Mircea Snegur said, among other things, that at 
the 
recent congress entitled Our Home, the Republic of Moldova, he 
mentioned, as he had done before, the same historical events and 
the need to preserve our brotherly ties, and, as he specified, 
to stick to our kin. 
  At the same congress, he emphasized that the policy promoted 
by the Republic of Moldova is consistent in all areas and is 
linked to reality and the nation's desire to consolidate its 
statehood and to develop as an independent state. 
  Speaking about the same policy, Snegur mentioned that the 
directions of economic and cultural integration between Moldova 
and Romania remain the same. 
  In connection with the Ilascu case, the Moldovan president 
said that he prefers to act rather than talk and that his 
intentions remain the same, namely to have these political 
detainees transferred to the constitutional legal bodies of the 
Republic of Moldova. 
  In connection with the meeting of the interministerial 
commission, recently held in Bucharest, Snegur affirmed that it 
has opened up very positive prospects for mutual economic 
cooperation. It is necessary to speed up and activate tangible 
relations between economic units; the meeting was assessed as 
encouraging for the future. 

</TEXT>

